description: System-generated unique identifier for this work order part line item.
Audit date/time when this record was created or last modified.
Indicates the part is managed in inventory rather than a miscellaneous entry; likely a boolean flag; confirm with SME.
Free-text description or catalog identifier for the part displayed on the work order line; confirm exact usage with SME.
User-entered notes relevant to this part line.
Extended line amount for the part (typically quantity × unit price, after any applicable adjustments).
Number of part units issued or used for the work order.
Unit price applied to the part on this line at time of issue/purchase.
Code indicating tax treatment for this line (e.g., taxable, exempt).
Lookup/reference describing the tax type code; confirm relationship with SME.
Markup or discount increment applied to the part’s price; likely percent or amount; confirm with SME.
Lookup/reference for the pricing increment setting; confirm with SME.
Identifier of the part in the parts catalog linked to this line; confirm with SME if unused when zero.
Lookup/reference to the parts catalog for the part identifier; confirm with SME.
Link to the receiving transaction detail that fulfilled this line; used when tied to a receipt/PO; confirm with SME.
Lookup/reference to the receiving detail source for recpartd; confirm with SME.
Internal key of the related work order header associated with this part line.
Reference indicating the relationship target for actwo (e.g., table/field name); confirm with SME.
Business work order number to which this part line belongs.
Lookup/reference to the work order header source for the workorder field.
Lifecycle state of the part line (for example, requested, issued, backordered, canceled).
Original identifier from a prior system for migration traceability.
Source table name from a prior system associated with legacykey.
Date/time when this part line record was initially created.
Internal cost basis for the part (e.g., average or standard cost) used for costing, not necessarily the sell price.
Quantity received using the quick-receive process for this line.
Finalized quantity resulting from quick-receive reconciliation; confirm with SME.
Cost captured during quick-receive for the received quantity on this line.
Final issued or received quantity recorded for this line after all adjustments; confirm with SME.
Controls whether only preassigned parts may be issued on this work order; confirm with SME.
Indicates the line was preallocated/templated (e.g., from PM/template) before actual issuance; confirm with SME.
Date associated with the current line status.
Transaction posting date for this part movement; confirm with SME.
Identifier of the user or process that created this line.
Lookup/reference to the user directory/source for created_by.
Accounting or cost bucket override to charge this line to a nondefault bucket; confirm with SME.
Lookup/reference to the bucket source for override_bucket.
Identifier of the specific inventory record/bin/lot from which the part was issued; confirm with SME.
Lookup/reference to the inventory source for partinv_ref.
Classification code for the part (e.g., filters, tires) used for reporting and accounting.
Lookup/reference to the category source for part_category.
Vendor identifier used during quick-receive for this line.
Lookup/reference to the vendor source for quick_rec_vendor.
Purchase order identifier or line reference associated with supplying this part.
Lookup/reference to the purchase order source for po_ref.
Inventory unit-of-measure code for this part (e.g., EA, BOX).
Lookup/reference to the unit-of-measure source for inventory_units.
Conversion factor between the inventory unit and the issue/use unit for this line.
Lookup/reference describing the conversion rule; confirm with SME.
Issue unit-of-measure code applied to this part line.
Lookup/reference to the unit-of-measure source for unit_type.
Estimated arrival date for ordered or backordered parts on this line.
Identifier linking the transaction to a barcode/scan capture event during issue or receipt; confirm with SME.
Lookup/reference to the scan session/source for partinv_scan; confirm with SME.
